y Luis de León (1527–91), he offers rich resources for interreligious engagement by believers in today’s religiously diverse world. Through an analysis of the documents of the 2019 Amazonian Synod, including Querida Amazonia, the Postsynodal Exhortation by Pope Francis, he explores a culture of encounter and dialogue that has been a hallmark of this pontificate. From the inscriptions in the caves of la Isla de Mona through the writings of the Latin American Bishops (CELAM), this book establishes a solid basis on which to discern the “Seeds of the Word” in our times.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aHispanic American theology. 4aHistory. 4aReligion. 4aTheology. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / Catholic.2bisacsh  aAmazonia.  aChristian Theology.  aHermeneutics.  aHistory.  aPope Francis.  aReligion.  aRevelation.1 aDíaz, Miguel H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNanko-Fernández, Carmen M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRiebe-Estrella, Gary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311075167340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781531505875?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781531505875423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781531505875/original  a978-3-11-075167-3  Fordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles